<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1654" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1654">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816.001Ar1/6.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At nine o’clock yesterday morning after trial and conviction by a
                            military court three of the assassins of President Araújo were publicly
                            shot in the Campo de Marte in the presence of many thousand
                            spectators.</p>
                        <p>The Government has informed me that perfect tranquility is reported to
                            exist throughout Salvador and that the signs portend a long period of
                            peace.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Heimke</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>